org.openimaj.image.typography

Class FontRenderer<T,Q extends FontStyle<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.typography.FontRenderer<T,Q>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of image pixels
    Q - type of FontStyle
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GeneralFontRenderer, MathMLFontRenderer

    public abstract class FontRenderer<T,Q extends FontStyle<T>>
extends Object
    The FontRenderer represents an object capable of rendering text with a given font and style to an image.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
